headlines.description: — Richaun Holmes had 25 points, 11 rebounds, three blocked shots and two steals, and the Sacramento Kings held on to beat Boston 107-96 on Friday night and earn their first season sweep of the Celtics since 2007.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings hold on, beat Celtics 107-96 to sweep season series

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson scored 23 points and grabbed a career-high 21 rebounds, and Dejounte Murray had 22 points as the San Antonio Spurs held on for a 116-110, wire-to-wire victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson has 23 points, 21 boards as Spurs beat Cavs 116-110

headlines.description: — Aaron Gordon scored a season-best 38 points, Evan Fournier added 31 and the Orlando Magic held off a furious fourth-quarter rally by the Brooklyn Nets to win 121-113 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon's 38 points lift Magic past Nets, 121-113

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored eight of his 31 points in the final minute and a half to lead the Utah Jazz to a 115-112 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell helps Jazz hold off Raptors, 115-112

headlines.description: — Frank Jackson had a season-high 23 points and the Detroit Pistons handed the Houston Rockets their franchise-record 19th straight loss, 113-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons hand Rockets franchise-worst 19th straight loss

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored a season-high 40 points, Jordan Poole added 25 while starting in place of injured Stephen Curry, and the short-handed Golden State Warriors beat the Memphis Grizzlies 116-103 on Friday night in the first of back-to-back...
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins scores 40 as short-handed Warriors beat Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 34 points, including a tying 3-pointer in the final second of regulation and a crucial jumper in the final seconds of overtime, lifting the Denver Nuggets past the Chicago Bulls 131-127 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 34 points, Nuggets beat Bulls 131-127 in OT

headlines.description: — Chris Paul scored 20 points, Devin Booker added 16 and the Phoenix Suns bounced back from a loss to the Minnesota Timberwolves the night before by beating them 113-101 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns bounce back from loss, beat Timberwolves 113-101

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 32 points, Damian Lillard had 31 and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Dallas Mavericks 125-119 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Lillard carry Blazers past Mavs, 125-119
